    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "For info (I'm subscribed to the rpy-dev list as well), this is almost certainly a tricky problem in rpy2 - there are somewhat inconsistent segfaults that seem to trigger on some systems but not others. And where segfaults can be reproduced, they can (at least in some cases) be reproduced outside of IPython.\n\nSo I think something IPython is doing is triggering the bug for @yang, but the bug itself is in rpy2.\n"
