    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Other people can trigger segfaults in various situations without IPython (see Artur's t.py script). So my money's certainly on rpy2, at least until those segfaults are fixed.\n\nAlso, IPython is 100% Python code, and any segfault indicates a bug in C code - either rpy2, or CPython itself.\n"
